Psychological bases of learning and teaching. Theories of learning and teaching, teaching models. Modern conception of learning and trends in pedagogics. Aims of pedagogics and patient education. The theoretical fundamentals of patient education. Application of pedagogical and methods in nursing. Learning and teaching in the study programme of nursing: establishing the purpose and plan for learning, the process of learning and teaching. Observation of learning and teaching, and analysing it. Practical planning of learning and teaching: constructing a lesson plan and presenting it.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop an understanding of the principles of learning and teaching, and guiding the process of learning. To develop skills to apply the principles of pedagogics and patient education in the various fields of nursing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: - understands the conceptions and principles of learning and teaching; - understands the aims of learning and teaching as they result from the theories of learning and teaching and the psychological bases of learning; - understands the principles of pedagogics and is able to apply them in the various fields of nursing; - is able to analyse the structure of the learning and teaching work and draw up a lesson plan.
